FBIS3-23329 "jptot011__l94145" JPRS-TOT-94-011-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 9 March 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY `Terrorists' Caught Preparing To Sabotage Industrial Plants TA0903162294 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1455 GMT 9 Mar 94 TA0903162294 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Kocaeli, Mar. 9 (A.A.) -- Security teams caught 12 separatist terrorists who were preparing to sabotage major industrial plants, including the oil refinery Tupras. The Anatolian News Agency learned that anti-terror teams carried out operations in Izmit and Golcuk, taking 12 people into custody, including an official of the terror organization. The 12 terrorists were determinedly involved in a recent terrorist raid in Tuzla train station, which killed five reserve officers, and various other terror incidents, including the killing of four people in Istanbul and extortion. [passage omitted]
